<font color="#FF0000">ISOLATION</font><br>
<tt>Sat Jan  4 10:55:54 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
My wife sent me off and then suffered for the year I was gone playing war. <br>
 She raised my kids, wrote encourging letters to me and never complaned or bought up the daily problems that I should have been there to share.<br><br>
It was only after my return, did she tell me what had happened.  She too was isolated.  Her &quot;friends&quot; and neighbors practicly ignored her--maybe the wifes were afraid that she would steal their husbands?<br><br>
In any case she was hurt by this but struggled on anyway.<br>
Once her name appeared in the local paper as the &quot;waiting wife.&quot;<br><br>
She received phone calls--reporting me KIA by some and others telling her that they hoped I'd be killed or maimed.<br><br>
Don't tell me she didn't suffer.<br><br>
She was braver then I was and no one gave her any medals either.<br>
Later, I gave her a miniture Purple Heart, framed.<br>
She'd earned it more then many.
